                <h1 class="ui header">The Application</h1>
                <p>
                    This project is a heated styling tool monitoring and control system. Temp data is collected every 10 minutes and at all times will have the last hour's worth of data stored.
                  Based on these readings if a heated device has been left on/heated for over 100 minutes, and if so, will automatically turn the device off. </p>
                <p>
                  The data is viewable in a mobile application, which shows the current temp, the temperature history, and the current device state.
                  The installed application will also send the user a push notification when the device has automatically switched off as described above. 
                  As an optional extra, the data can also be accessed and displayed in graph format on this companion web application, which can allow users to monitor multiple devices. 
                </p>
